Step 1. Calculate Gross Profit Margin  
• From the income statement:  
 – Gross Profit = 291843.79  
 – Total Revenue = 836813.79  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
 = (291843.79 / 836813.79) × 100  
 ≈ 34.88%

Step 2. Calculate Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
• From the cash flow statement:  
 – Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -1919526.63  
• From the balance sheet, identify current liabilities:  
 – Accounts Payable = 5596070.00  
 – Taxes Payable = 41840.70  
 – Total Current Liabilities = 5596070.00 + 41840.70 = 5637910.70  
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Current Liabilities)  
 = -1919526.63 / 5637910.70  
 ≈ -0.34

Thus, the answer is:
{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "34.88%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-0.34"
  }
}
